- IF I WERE A LITTLE
BIT YOUNGER,

30
00:02:40,375 --> 00:02:41,833
I'D LOCK THE DOORS ON THIS PLACE

31
00:02:41,916 --> 00:02:43,708
AND CHECK IT OUT WITH YOU BOYS.

32
00:02:44,500 --> 00:02:45,500
- ( car honks )

33
00:02:46,875 --> 00:02:47,833
- BE RIGHT THERE.

34
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:56,333
- I ALWAYS HIT THESE RED LIGHTS
WHEN I'M IN A FREAKING HURRY.

35
00:02:56,416 --> 00:02:58,666
- IS THAT, UH,
KENJI, LOOK.

36
00:03:00,083 --> 00:03:02,375
ISN'T THAT TAKUMI'S GIRLFRIEND?

37
00:03:02,458 --> 00:03:04,958
- YEAH, SURE AS HELL
LOOKS LIKE HER.

38
00:03:05,041 --> 00:03:08,000
MAYBE SHE'S INTERVIEWING FOR
A PART TIME JOB AT FAST BURGER.

39
00:03:09,333 --> 00:03:10,291
- ( tires screeching )

40
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:33,958
- ( gasps )

41
00:03:35,291 --> 00:03:36,583
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

42
00:03:36,666 --> 00:03:37,625
- ITSUKI?

43
00:03:38,375 --> 00:03:39,666
- SERIOUSLY, WHAT'S UP?

44
00:03:39,750 --> 00:03:41,416
- THERE'S JUST A WHOLE
LOT THAT'S GONE DOWN

45
00:03:41,500 --> 00:03:42,916
SINCE LAST NIGHT.

46
00:03:44,458 --> 00:03:46,333
- YOU MIGHT'VE BEEN THE ONE
WHO CHOSE THIS LOCATION,

47
00:03:46,416 --> 00:03:48,208
BUT I'M THE ONE WHO KNOWS IT.

48
00:03:49,833 --> 00:03:52,916
KAZUMI. I WANT YOU
TO STAY HERE WHILE I'M GONE.

49
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:55,000
- BUT WHY?
- 'CAUSE I SAID SO.

50
00:03:55,083 --> 00:03:57,250
YOU CAN CATCH A BUS OR TRAIN
OUT OF HERE IN THE MORNING

51
00:03:57,333 --> 00:03:58,791
IF YOU HAVE TO.

52
00:03:58,875 --> 00:04:00,916
THAT WAY IF ANYTHING SHOULD
HAPPEN TO EITHER OF OUR CARS,

53
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,625
AT LEAST YOU WON'T
BE STUCK OUT HERE

54
00:04:02,708 --> 00:04:04,500
WITHOUT A WAY TO GET BACK HOME.

55
00:04:04,583 --> 00:04:05,833
- TAKUMI, WHAT IS THIS?

56
00:04:08,416 --> 00:04:09,750
- YOU'RE GOING THERE,
AREN'T YOU?

57
00:04:09,833 --> 00:04:11,500
YOU'RE GOING OUT
TO SHOMARU PASS.

58
00:04:11,583 --> 00:04:13,041
YOU KNOW YOU SHOULDN'T
RACE THERE.

59
00:04:13,125 --> 00:04:14,708
I'M BEGGIN' YOU.
PICK SOMEPLACE ELSE.

60
00:04:14,791 --> 00:04:16,041
- THAT'S ENOUGH ALREADY.

61
00:04:16,125 --> 00:04:18,083
THIS IS NONE OF YOUR
BUSINESS ANYWAY.

62
00:04:18,166 --> 00:04:19,583
- BUT WATARU.

63
00:04:19,666 --> 00:04:21,375
- JUST SO YOU'RE AWARE OF WHAT
WE'RE ABOUT TO DRIVE INTO.

64
00:04:21,458 --> 00:04:23,833
THIS PASS IS NARROW AND TRICKY
LIKE YOU WOULDN'T EVEN BELIEVE.

65
00:04:23,916 --> 00:04:25,666
THERE'S NOT ANOTHER PASS
LIKE IT ANYWHERE.

66
00:04:25,750 --> 00:04:27,000
I'LL TAKE THE LEAD
ON THE FIRST RUN

67
00:04:27,083 --> 00:04:28,708
SO YOU CAN SEE WHAT'S GOING ON.

68
00:04:28,791 --> 00:04:30,333
SINCE THIS IS YOUR
FIRST TIME UP HERE,

69
00:04:30,416 --> 00:04:33,375
I THINK WE REALLY NEED TO TAKE
SOME PRECAUTIONS, OKAY?

70
00:04:33,458 --> 00:04:35,583
AFTER THE FIRST RUN, WE'LL
ALTERNATE POSITIONS

71
00:04:35,666 --> 00:04:36,916
AND KEEP DOING SO

72
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:39,333
UNTIL ONE OF US PULLS AWAY
OR PASSES THE OTHER GUY.

73
00:04:40,458 --> 00:04:42,458
IT'LL BE A SUDDEN DEATH RACE.
GOT THAT?

74
00:04:42,541 --> 00:04:44,125
AND SINCE WE'RE PROBABLY
EQUALLY SKILLED

75
00:04:44,208 --> 00:04:46,666
SOME OTHER ELEMENT
WILL BE THE DECIDING FACTOR.

76
00:04:46,750 --> 00:04:49,291
- YEAH? WHAT OTHER
ELEMENT WOULD THAT BE?

77
00:04:49,375 --> 00:04:52,500
- LUCK, STAMINA, COMPATIBILITY
WITH THE CAR, WITH THE ROAD.

78
00:04:52,583 --> 00:04:54,041
IT COULD BE ANYTHING.

79
00:04:54,125 --> 00:04:55,500
WE SHOULD ROLL OUT NOW.

80
00:04:55,583 --> 00:04:57,375
WHEN WE GET THERE,
I'LL TURN ON MY HAZARD LIGHTS

81
00:04:57,458 --> 00:04:59,333
TO LET YOU KNOW
AND THEN WE GET STARTED.

82
00:05:07,958 --> 00:05:09,166
- ( engine revs )

83
00:05:16,875 --> 00:05:17,875
- Itsuki: TAKUMI.

84
00:05:20,750 --> 00:05:22,791
I WONDER IF TAKUMI KNEW
THAT KAZUMI WOULD BE

85
00:05:22,875 --> 00:05:24,708
COMING UP WITH HER BROTHER.

86
00:05:31,375 --> 00:05:34,583
- IS SHOMARU PASS REALLY
AS DANGEROUS AS YOU WERE SAYING?

87
00:05:34,666 --> 00:05:36,875
- FOR STARTERS,
IT'S A REALLY OLD ROAD.

88
00:05:36,958 --> 00:05:39,625
AND IT'S NOT THAT LONG
BUT YOU GO UPHILL FIRST,

89
00:05:39,708 --> 00:05:40,791
THEN FROM THE MIDDLE POINT,

90
00:05:40,875 --> 00:05:42,750
YOU START TO GO INTO THE
DOWNHILL SECTION.

91
00:05:42,833 --> 00:05:45,208
- SO, THEN IT'S LIKE
A HALF UPHILL COURSE?

92
00:05:45,291 --> 00:05:47,125
- THAT'S HARDLY
ALL OF THE PROBLEMS.

93
00:05:47,208 --> 00:05:49,625
IT'S NARROW, IT'S GOT
HORRIBLE VISIBILITY

94
00:05:49,708 --> 00:05:50,958
AND THAT COMBO HAS CAUSED,

95
00:05:51,041 --> 00:05:52,958
I DON'T KNOW, HOW MANY
ACCIDENTS OVER THE YEARS.

96
00:05:53,041 --> 00:05:54,708
THE GUARDRAILS ARE ALL RUSTED.

97
00:05:54,791 --> 00:05:56,833
THE ROAD'S UNEVEN AND SLIPPERY.

98
00:05:56,916 --> 00:06:00,375
EVEN WATARU'S HAD TWO ACCIDENTS
THERE OVER THE PAST FEW YEARS.

99
00:06:00,458 --> 00:06:02,208
HE SAID IT WAS ONE
OF THE TOUGHEST PASSES

100
00:06:02,291 --> 00:06:04,083
THAT HE'S EVER HAD TO RACE.

101
00:06:04,166 --> 00:06:07,333
- FOR REAL? AND THIS IS TAKUMI'S
FIRST TIME GOING UP THERE.

102
00:06:07,416 --> 00:06:08,666
IT'S TOO MUCH FOR HIM.

103
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:21,291
- THERE'S HIS HAZARD'S.
THIS IS IT.

104
00:06:21,375 --> 00:06:22,750
- HOPE YOU'RE READY.

105
00:06:22,833 --> 00:06:25,208
- DON'T WANT YOU TO CRASH
YOUR PRECIOUS CAR JUST YET.

106
00:06:32,625 --> 00:06:33,666
- IT'S AN UPHILL.

107
00:06:39,666 --> 00:06:40,750
- WHAT IS THAT?

108
00:06:44,375 --> 00:06:46,958
- I TOLD YOU THIS WOULD
BE ONE HELL OF A TRIP.

109
00:06:47,041 --> 00:06:48,416
IT'S A GREAT ENGINE
YOU GOT THERE.

110
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:50,833
HELL, YOU CAN EVEN
KEEP UP WITH ME ON THIS HILL.

111
00:06:50,916 --> 00:06:53,208
GUESS THERE'S NO NEED TO TAKE
IT EASY ON YOU, IS THERE?

112
00:07:02,250 --> 00:07:03,333
- Natsuki: SEE YOU
GUYS TOMORROW.

113
00:07:03,416 --> 00:07:04,625
- Man: YEAH,
GOOD NIGHT, NATSUKI.

114
00:07:09,083 --> 00:07:11,166
- I'M SORRY ABOUT
EVERYTHING, TAKUMI.

115
00:07:12,125 --> 00:07:14,083
I'M THE ONE TO BLAME
IN ALL OF THIS.

116
00:07:16,291 --> 00:07:18,083
I KNOW THAT NOW.

117
00:07:18,166 --> 00:07:19,416
BUT I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO FIX IT.

118
00:07:20,375 --> 00:07:22,416
SO FOR THE TIME BEING,

119
00:07:22,500 --> 00:07:25,666
I'M JUST GOING TO TRY WORKING
PART TIME LIKE YOU DO.

120
00:07:25,750 --> 00:07:28,416
I THINK THAT'S THE BEST
I CAN COME UP WITH.

121
00:07:28,500 --> 00:07:30,791
I'M GOING TO TAKE
THIS TIME IN MY LIFE

122
00:07:30,875 --> 00:07:33,000
TO BECOME A DIFFERENT PERSON.

123
00:07:40,041 --> 00:07:41,166
- ( tires screeching )

124
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:45,500
- I DRIVE THIS EIGHT-SIX
FOR ONE REASON.

125
00:07:45,583 --> 00:07:48,250
BECAUSE DEFEATING ANY OPPONENT
I'M UP AGAINST WITH AN OLD CAR,

126
00:07:48,333 --> 00:07:49,708
EVERYONE THINKS
IS SUCH A PIECE,

127
00:07:49,791 --> 00:07:51,583
MAKES THE WIN ALL THE
MORE SATISFYING.

128
00:07:51,666 --> 00:07:54,333
BUT THIS TIME, SOMETHING
IS DIFFERENT FOR ME.

129
00:07:54,416 --> 00:07:57,916
I CANNOT LOSE TO ANOTHER
EIGHT-SIX NO MATTER WHAT.

130
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:00,708
THIS IS MORE PRESSURE THAN
I'VE FELT IN ANY OTHER RACE.

131
00:08:02,375 --> 00:08:03,708
THAT'S CRAZY.

132
00:08:03,791 --> 00:08:05,041
I CAN EVEN SEE THE AURA

133
00:08:05,125 --> 00:08:07,791
RADIATING FROM YOUR
TRUENO, TAKUMI.

134
00:08:12,500 --> 00:08:14,916
- Kenta: YOU REALLY THINK
THIS IS A GOOD SPOT, KEISUKE?

135
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,166
- THE COURSE IS
SO DAMN NARROW.

136
00:08:16,250 --> 00:08:17,708
THERE'S REALLY NO
OTHER PLACE TO WATCH.

137
00:08:17,791 --> 00:08:19,458
THIS IS THE BEST WE GOT, MAN.

138
00:08:21,125 --> 00:08:22,166
- HERE THEY COME.

139
00:08:31,791 --> 00:08:33,458
- YEAH. THIS IS IT.

140
00:08:38,125 --> 00:08:40,166
THAT SUDDEN BOOST OF
POWER IS THE BEST THING

141
00:08:40,250 --> 00:08:42,291
THIS CAR HAS TO OFFER.

142
00:08:43,541 --> 00:08:44,791
- ( engine revving )

143
00:08:49,583 --> 00:08:52,333
- THERE GOES THAT OBSOLETE
"BOOM" TURBO OF HIS.

144
00:08:52,416 --> 00:08:53,791
- HEY, I GOT A QUESTION.

145
00:08:53,875 --> 00:08:55,625
AREN'T TAKUMI'S TRUENO
AND WATARU'S LEVIN

146
00:08:55,708 --> 00:08:57,166
BASICALLY THE SAME CAR?

147
00:08:57,250 --> 00:08:59,000
I MEAN, MY UNDERSTANDING IS
THAT THEY GOT DIFFERENT HEADLAMP

148
00:08:59,083 --> 00:09:00,083
AND TAIL LAMP DESIGNS,

149
00:09:00,166 --> 00:09:01,708
BUT THAT'S PRETTY MUCH
WHERE IT STOPS.

150
00:09:01,791 --> 00:09:03,083
SO WHY DO YOU THINK
THE TWO OF THEM

151
00:09:03,166 --> 00:09:04,625
ARE RUNNING SO DIFFERENTLY
OUT THERE?

152
00:09:04,708 --> 00:09:07,416
- WELL, THAT'S BECAUSE, YA KNOW.

153
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:09,083
I THINK MY BROTHER WOULD
DO A BETTER JOB

154
00:09:09,166 --> 00:09:11,083
OF EXPLAINING IT TO
YOU THAN I WOULD.

155
00:09:11,166 --> 00:09:12,666
I UNDERSTAND IT IN MY HEAD

156
00:09:12,750 --> 00:09:15,875
BUT I JUST CAN'T PUT THAT CRAP
INTO WORDS AS GOOD AS HE CAN.

157
00:09:15,958 --> 00:09:17,125
- IT'S LIKE YOU
WERE SAYING, KENTA,

158
00:09:17,208 --> 00:09:19,791
THE LEVIN AND THE TRUENO
ARE LIKE TWIN SIBLINGS.

159
00:09:19,875 --> 00:09:23,250
EXCEPT THEIR ENGINES TAKE
DIFFERENT TUNING METHODS.

160
00:09:23,333 --> 00:09:24,791
THIS, OF COURSE,
CAUSES THEM TO RUN

161
00:09:24,875 --> 00:09:27,541
LIKE TWO COMPLETELY
DIFFERENT CARS.

162
00:09:27,625 --> 00:09:29,125
THE METHOD THAT GETS
USED IN THE CAR

163
00:09:29,208 --> 00:09:30,500
WITHOUT THE TURBOCHARGER

164
00:09:30,583 --> 00:09:32,500
IS CALLED MECHANICAL TUNING.
IT'S COMMON.

165
00:09:33,666 --> 00:09:35,250
THAT'S TAKUMI'S TRUENO.

166
00:09:38,291 --> 00:09:41,833
HIS FOOT ON THE GAS PEDAL
CONTROLS THE RPM'S DIRECTLY.

167
00:09:41,916 --> 00:09:43,750
IT'S INSTANT RESPONSE
IS IT'S STRENGTH.

168
00:09:45,750 --> 00:09:48,750
EVEN AFTER ENTERING A CORNER
AT NEARLY TOP SPEED,

169
00:09:48,833 --> 00:09:50,875
HE CAN STILL MAKE
ADJUSTMENTS TO HIS ATTACK.

170
00:09:50,958 --> 00:09:52,041
A NICE ADVANTAGE.

171
00:09:53,125 --> 00:09:54,833
- ( tires screeching )

172
00:09:54,916 --> 00:09:57,000
THAT MEANS HE CAN ATTACK
THE CORNERS MORE AGGRESSIVELY

173
00:09:57,083 --> 00:09:58,916
THAN THE CAR WITH
THE TURBO EVER COULD.

174
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:00,958
WHEN IT COMES TO
ENTERING CORNERS,

175
00:10:01,041 --> 00:10:03,583
CARS LIKE THIS ARE THE
BEST ON THE ROAD.

176
00:10:03,666 --> 00:10:06,375
ON THE OTHER HAND,
THE LEVIN IS A TURBO.

177
00:10:06,458 --> 00:10:08,625
IT MIGHT BE A HAIR SLOWER
WHEN IT COMES TO THE CORNERS,

178
00:10:08,708 --> 00:10:10,583
BUT THE ACCELERATION IT HAS
ON THE STRAIGHTAWAYS

179
00:10:10,666 --> 00:10:13,041
COVERS THAT DIFFERENCE
IN SPADES.

180
00:10:15,875 --> 00:10:18,833
CARS WITH TURBO
ARE BEST AT EXITING CORNERS.

181
00:10:18,916 --> 00:10:20,958
- THEN WHAT ABOUT
THE LEVIN'S FISHTAILING?

182
00:10:21,041 --> 00:10:22,958
COULDN'T THAT BECOME
A BIG PROBLEM?

183
00:10:23,041 --> 00:10:25,000
- THE 'BOOM' TURBO
TENDS TO LAG A BIT,

184
00:10:25,083 --> 00:10:26,750
SO ONCE THE BOOST
PRESSURE GOES DOWN,

185
00:10:26,833 --> 00:10:28,625
IT TAKES SOME TIME
TO WORK IT BACK UP.

186
00:10:28,708 --> 00:10:31,083
WHICH IS SOMETHING, THE DRIVER
SHOULD KNOW HOW TO DO.

187
00:10:31,166 --> 00:10:32,875
THAT'S WHY HE KEEPS HIS
FOOT ON THE GAS

188
00:10:32,958 --> 00:10:34,250
WHEN HE'S EXITING THE CORNERS

189
00:10:34,333 --> 00:10:36,625
AND CONTROLS THE VEHICLE
USING COUNTER-STEERING ONLY.

190
00:10:39,041 --> 00:10:41,708
THAT'S WHAT HIS FISHTAILING
TECHNIQUE IS ALL ABOUT.

191
00:10:41,791 --> 00:10:43,833
IT'S SO HE COULD DEAL WITH
ALL THE PECULIAR DETAILS

192
00:10:43,916 --> 00:10:45,041
HIS CAR HAS.

193
00:10:45,125 --> 00:10:46,833
WHICH I'M SURE ARE QUITE
A FEW BY THIS POINT.

194
00:10:46,916 --> 00:10:48,458
- THAT SPELL IT OUT FOR YOU?

195
00:10:48,541 --> 00:10:51,250
LISTEN, PASS RACING IS NOT
JUST A TOUCH AND GO SPORT.

196
00:10:51,333 --> 00:10:53,791
- I GOT IT. AT LEAST
I THINK I'M UNDERSTANDING.

197
00:10:58,541 --> 00:10:59,666
- ( tires screeching )

