206
00:11:51,041 --> 00:11:52,625
- WHAT THE HELL
WAS UP WITH THAT?

207
00:12:09,375 --> 00:12:11,666
- ARE YOU CERTAIN THIS IS
WHERE WE'RE SUPPOSED TO BE?

208
00:12:12,166 --> 00:12:13,666
- YEAH. I THINK.

209
00:12:13,750 --> 00:12:15,416
THAT'S WHAT HE TOLD ME.

210
00:12:15,500 --> 00:12:16,791
- WHAT'S THAT SOUND?

211
00:12:16,875 --> 00:12:18,166
- ( engines revving )

212
00:12:19,666 --> 00:12:20,666
- THAT'S THEM.

213
00:12:51,458 --> 00:12:53,416
- NO WAY.
THAT WAS A "BOOM" TURBO.

214
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:55,208
- IT LOOKS OUT OF CONTROL,
THE WAY IT'S MOVING.

215
00:12:55,291 --> 00:12:56,583
THAT'S GOT TO BE DANGEROUS.

216
00:12:56,666 --> 00:12:58,666
THE ROAD'S SO NARROW,
HE'S BARELY STAYING ON IT.

217
00:12:58,750 --> 00:13:00,458
LIKE HE'S SLIDING DOWN
THE EDGE OF A KNIFE.

218
00:13:00,541 --> 00:13:03,625
- BUT MAN, WHEN HE'S ON, HE'S
FASTER THAN ANY CAR OUT THERE.

219
00:13:03,708 --> 00:13:05,375
HE'S A DIFFERENT KIND
OF OPPONENT.

220
00:13:05,458 --> 00:13:08,333
THE KIND THAT BREAKS EVERY
CONVENTIONAL RULE ON THE BOOKS.

221
00:13:12,916 --> 00:13:14,875
- SECOND ROUND AND THIS TIME,

222
00:13:14,958 --> 00:13:17,416
I'LL BE THE ONE IN THE
OBSERVER'S POSITION.

223
00:13:17,500 --> 00:13:20,291
I GET TO SEE WHAT YOUR
UNDEFEATED GUNMA-GROWN TALENT

224
00:13:20,375 --> 00:13:21,750
HAS TO OFFER.

225
00:13:26,791 --> 00:13:29,500
- THIS AGAIN.
MAN, THIS CORNER SUCKS.

226
00:13:33,791 --> 00:13:35,500
- RIGHT NOW, EVERY ELEMENT
THAT COULD LINE UP

227
00:13:35,583 --> 00:13:38,375
AGAINST TAKUMI IS
DOING EXACTLY THAT.

228
00:13:38,458 --> 00:13:41,666
A HORRIBLY TRICKY COURSE
THAT HE'S GOT NO EXPERIENCE ON.

229
00:13:41,750 --> 00:13:43,416
THEN THERE'S THE LEVIN'S
IRREGULAR PACE

230
00:13:43,500 --> 00:13:45,750
THAT JUMPS IN AND
BREAKS HIS RHYTHM.

231
00:13:46,958 --> 00:13:48,083
BUT ABOVE
EVERYTHING ELSE,

232
00:13:48,166 --> 00:13:50,333
HE'S GOT THAT BIG UNEASY
FEELING IN HIS GUT.

233
00:13:50,416 --> 00:13:52,375
HE'S STILL NOT USED
TO THE NEW EIGHT-SIX.

234
00:13:52,458 --> 00:13:54,583
HER HANDLING'S STILL
A MYSTERY TO HIM

235
00:13:54,666 --> 00:13:56,458
AND THAT'S HIS BIGGEST HANDICAP.

236
00:13:59,333 --> 00:14:00,750
- THESE CONDITIONS ARE CRAP.

237
00:14:00,833 --> 00:14:02,666
MY CAR IS SHAKING
ALL OVER THE PLACE.

238
00:14:06,333 --> 00:14:08,458
I CAN'T EVEN USE THE INNER
EDGE OF THE ROAD.

239
00:14:08,541 --> 00:14:10,916
IT'S WORN ALL TO HELL.

240
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:13,291
IF THE TIRES CATCH IT,
THEY'RE JUST GOING TO SLIP.

241
00:14:15,375 --> 00:14:16,875
AND I CAN'T USE THE
FREAKING OUTER EDGE

242
00:14:16,958 --> 00:14:18,583
COMING OUT OF THE
CORNERS EITHER.

243
00:14:18,666 --> 00:14:20,708
THERE AREN'T NEARLY AS MANY
USABLE AREAS ON THIS ROAD

244
00:14:20,791 --> 00:14:22,791
AS YOU'D THINK BY LOOKING AT IT.

245
00:14:29,541 --> 00:14:32,500
- TAKUMI, IF YOU HADN'T FIGURED
IT OUT, YOU BETTER FAST.

246
00:14:32,583 --> 00:14:34,916
THE SUSPENSION SETTINGS
CHANGE BASED ON THE POWER

247
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:36,333
COMING OUT OF THE ENGINE.

248
00:14:36,416 --> 00:14:38,708
AFTER I INSTALLED THE NEW
ONE, YOU KEPT SAYING TO ME

249
00:14:38,791 --> 00:14:40,916
YOU COULDN'T CORNER
LIKE YOU USED TO BE ABLE TO

250
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:43,750
WHICH MAKES PERFECT SENSE.

251
00:14:43,833 --> 00:14:47,125
BECAUSE THAT'S EXACTLY HOW I
SET THE CAR UP FROM THE GET-GO.

252
00:14:49,666 --> 00:14:52,750
ONLY BY GETTING YOUR CAR
REVVED UP TO THE HIGHEST RPM'S,

253
00:14:52,833 --> 00:14:55,625
WILL YOU BE ABLE TO CORNER AT
THE HIGHER SPEED LIKE YOU WANT.

254
00:14:57,875 --> 00:14:59,583
YOU NEED TO PICK UP
ON THAT, SON.

255
00:14:59,666 --> 00:15:03,250
UNLOCK THAT CAR'S CAPABILITIES
AND THIS RACE IS YOURS.

256
00:15:07,791 --> 00:15:09,125
- WHAT'S GOING ON?

257
00:15:09,208 --> 00:15:10,500
DID I JUST IMAGINE THAT?

258
00:15:23,375 --> 00:15:24,916
- Wataru: THE TURBO IN
THIS BABY'S SO FAST,

259
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:26,875
I'M HONESTLY
SWEATING A BIT.

260
00:15:26,958 --> 00:15:29,250
THIS CAR IS NOTHING
LIKE IT WAS BEFORE.

261
00:15:31,333 --> 00:15:32,875
I MEAN, SURE, I'LL HAVE
TO GO AT HER

262
00:15:32,958 --> 00:15:34,875
WITH MORE DETAILED MAINTENANCE.

263
00:15:34,958 --> 00:15:36,125
AND EVEN WHEN I'M RACING,

264
00:15:36,208 --> 00:15:38,541
I'M GONNA HAVE TO KEEP
ONE EYE ON MY GAUGES.

265
00:15:38,625 --> 00:15:41,000
THIS RIDE COST A LOT
OF MONEY AND SWEAT

266
00:15:41,083 --> 00:15:44,333
BUT I DON'T REGRET A SINGLE
THING ABOUT ANY OF IT.

267
00:15:44,416 --> 00:15:46,833
FINALLY GOT THE POWER UNDER
THIS HOOD I'VE DREAMED OF.

268
00:15:47,875 --> 00:15:49,291
HEAR THAT, KAZUMI?

269
00:15:49,375 --> 00:15:51,375
I KEEP GROWING 'CAUSE IT
ALL MEANS NOTHING

270
00:15:51,458 --> 00:15:53,541
THE SECOND YOU STOP.

271
00:15:53,625 --> 00:15:55,291
YOU KEEP UP WITH
THIS RUNNING AWAY

272
00:15:55,375 --> 00:15:56,916
FROM THE THINGS YOU
SUCK AT ROUTINE

273
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:58,833
AND YOU'LL NEVER BE
GOOD AT ANYTHING.

274
00:15:58,916 --> 00:16:01,666
YOU JUST HAVE TO KEEP SEARCHING
FOR WHAT YOU ARE GOOD AT.

275
00:16:01,750 --> 00:16:03,916
AND KEEP MOVING FORWARD
ON YOUR OWN TWO FEET.

276
00:16:06,416 --> 00:16:07,916
- WATARU.

277
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:08,958
- YOU THIRSTY?

278
00:16:11,041 --> 00:16:14,000
- OH, THANKS. THAT'S NICE.
IT'S WARM.

279
00:16:16,833 --> 00:16:18,125
- LISTEN, ITSUKI.

280
00:16:18,750 --> 00:16:20,250
- WHAT'S UP?

281
00:16:20,333 --> 00:16:22,958
- I DON'T THINK THAT,
THAT AFTER TODAY,

282
00:16:23,041 --> 00:16:24,875
I DON'T THINK
I'M GOING BACK TO GUNMA.

283
00:16:25,750 --> 00:16:28,500
SO, UH, I JUST...

284
00:16:28,583 --> 00:16:31,916
I DON'T WANT TO SAY IT BUT THIS
WILL PROBABLY BE GOODBYE FOR US.

285
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:33,333
I AM SORRY.

286
00:16:33,416 --> 00:16:34,458
- WHAT?

287
00:16:40,625 --> 00:16:43,208
- MY PARENTS FOUND OUT ABOUT ME
LEAVING WORK THE OTHER DAY.

288
00:16:43,291 --> 00:16:44,916
THEY'RE ACTUALLY PRETTY
TICKED OFF AT ME.

289
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:46,625
I'M ALL KINDS OF GROUNDED.

290
00:16:46,708 --> 00:16:50,208
BUT THAT'S NOT REALLY THE
REASON WHY I'M LEAVING GUNMA.

291
00:16:50,291 --> 00:16:52,250
I WAS THINKING IN THE CAR
ON THE WAY UP HERE.

292
00:16:52,333 --> 00:16:54,416
AND THE ONE THING
I COULDN'T KEEP OUT OF MY HEAD

293
00:16:54,500 --> 00:16:57,583
WAS THE IDEA THAT I NEED
TO CHOOSE MY OWN PATH.

294
00:16:57,666 --> 00:17:00,041
BECAUSE IF I'M THE ONLY ONE
WHO CHOOSES IT,

295
00:17:00,125 --> 00:17:02,333
THEN I'LL ALWAYS BE ABLE TO SAY
TO MYSELF IN THE END

296
00:17:02,416 --> 00:17:04,458
THAT I WAS RIGHT
ABOUT WHATEVER I DECIDED.

297
00:17:06,833 --> 00:17:10,458
THAT STUPID OLD JOB THAT I HAD,
AND THIS TEMPORARY ONE,

298
00:17:10,541 --> 00:17:12,791
WELL THEY WERE NEVER MY IDEA.

299
00:17:12,875 --> 00:17:16,125
I NEED TO GET OUT THERE
AND FIND A JOB FOR MYSELF.

300
00:17:16,208 --> 00:17:18,416
AND I ALSO HAVE
SOMETHING ELSE I WANNA DO.

301
00:17:21,208 --> 00:17:22,666
- SO, WHAT IS IT?

302
00:17:22,750 --> 00:17:23,916
- I WANNA SAVE UP
ENOUGH MONEY

303
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:26,750
SO I CAN GET MY DRIVER'S
LICENSE JUST LIKE YOU.

304
00:17:26,833 --> 00:17:29,625
IT'LL BE MY FIRST STEP
TOWARDS REAL INDEPENDENCE.

305
00:17:35,916 --> 00:17:38,458
I WAS WRONG TO THINK THAT
MOVING TO SOME FARAWAY PLACE

306
00:17:38,541 --> 00:17:40,458
WAS GOING TO SOLVE
ALL MY PROBLEMS.

307
00:17:40,541 --> 00:17:42,958
HOLDING THE STEERING WHEEL IN
YOUR LIFE SOUNDS A LOT BETTER

308
00:17:43,041 --> 00:17:45,333
THAN BEING A PASSENGER
AND WATCHING SOMEONE ELSE DO IT.

309
00:17:46,250 --> 00:17:47,958
I WANT TO RUN MY OWN LIFE.

310
00:17:48,041 --> 00:17:49,416
AND I WANT TO BE ABLE TO DO IT

311
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:51,958
WITHOUT ANYONE ELSE
JUMPING IN TO HELP.

312
00:17:52,041 --> 00:17:55,291
- UH, KAZUMI?
I, UH, I THOUGHT...

313
00:17:55,375 --> 00:17:57,791
- YOU THOUGHT IT WAS
BECAUSE OF YOU BUT IT'S NOT.

314
00:17:57,875 --> 00:18:00,791
I WON'T GO BACK TO GUNMA 'CAUSE
I CAN'T GET MY LICENSE THERE.

315
00:18:00,875 --> 00:18:03,166
- OH, THAT'S RIGHT.

316
00:18:04,958 --> 00:18:06,791
- I CAN'T THANK YOU
ENOUGH, ITSUKI.

317
00:18:07,333 --> 00:18:08,375
YOU'RE THE BEST.

318
00:18:11,416 --> 00:18:13,708
- I CAN'T BELIEVE THIS.

319
00:18:13,791 --> 00:18:16,083
I'VE FALLEN IN LOVE
WITH YOU, KAZUMI.

320
00:18:20,958 --> 00:18:22,458
- HEY, HERE COMES
THE SECOND ROUND.

321
00:18:22,541 --> 00:18:23,750
- ( tires screeching )

322
00:18:31,333 --> 00:18:32,541
- I THINK THE KID IS
FINALLY STARTING

323
00:18:32,625 --> 00:18:34,208
TO GET USED TO HIS NEW ENGINE.

324
00:18:35,416 --> 00:18:38,166
IT'S TIME FOR THIS EIGHT-SIX
TO OPEN IT'S EYES TO A NEW LIFE.

325
00:18:43,541 --> 00:18:46,250
- I CAN CONTROL HER BETTER.
IT'S A LOT EASIER NOW.

326
00:18:48,041 --> 00:18:50,083
I WAS JUST STRUGGLING
WITH THIS YESTERDAY

327
00:18:53,333 --> 00:18:55,416
IS IT BECAUSE I'M GIVING
HER MORE POWER?

328
00:18:57,416 --> 00:18:58,708
WHO CARES?

329
00:18:58,791 --> 00:19:01,083
NOW THAT I CAN CONTROL HER,
I CAN RUN MY RACE.

330
00:19:02,708 --> 00:19:04,000
THIS IS MY TIME.

331
00:19:04,083 --> 00:19:05,916
I MIGHT JUST BE ABLE
TO PULL THIS OFF.

332
00:19:09,291 --> 00:19:11,791
- I WAS JUST PLANNING ON PLAYING
THE OBSERVER THIS ROUND,

333
00:19:11,875 --> 00:19:14,375
BUT THAT'S CLEARLY NOT
GOING TO WORK ANYMORE.

334
00:19:14,458 --> 00:19:16,375
HE'S ADAPTING
TO THIS COURSE FAST.

335
00:19:16,458 --> 00:19:17,875
A LOT QUICKER
THAN I WOULD'VE THOUGHT.

336
00:19:17,958 --> 00:19:20,125
THERE'S NOT A FIRST TIMER I KNOW
OF WHO COULD'VE RACED HERE

337
00:19:20,208 --> 00:19:22,333
AND TAKEN IT ON
THIS WELL THIS FAST.

338
00:19:22,416 --> 00:19:23,833
IT'S IMPRESSIVE AS HELL.

339
00:19:23,916 --> 00:19:26,708
I CAN'T BELIEVE THAT RACERS
LIKE HIM ACTUALLY EXIST.

340
00:19:26,791 --> 00:19:30,583
BUT SO WHAT? I'M STILL NOT
GOING TO LOSE ON MY OWN TURF.

341
00:19:30,666 --> 00:19:33,125
THIS BITCH OF A RACE
IS JUST GETTING STARTED.

342
00:19:39,333 --> 00:19:41,958
- MAKE SURE YOU REV IT UP
TO ELEVEN THOUSAND RPM'S.

343
00:19:53,208 --> 00:19:54,666
- ( tires screeching )

344
00:20:01,333 --> 00:20:03,500
- THERE'S NOTHING COOLER
THAN GOOD PASS RACERS.

345
00:20:04,708 --> 00:20:07,458
AND YOU'RE NOT BAD, TAKUMI.

346
00:20:07,541 --> 00:20:09,125
YOU GOT SOME
SHARP ASS TECHNIQUES

347
00:20:09,208 --> 00:20:11,250
THAT WOULD CONVINCE
ANYONE OF YOUR SKILLS.

348
00:20:11,333 --> 00:20:14,291
WHICH MEANS I CAN KICK ALL OF
THE FIRE OUT OF MY LEVIN.

349
00:20:19,375 --> 00:20:20,875
THIS IS JUST THE
KIND OF EXCITEMENT

350
00:20:20,958 --> 00:20:22,166
I'VE BEEN LOOKING FOR.

351
00:20:22,250 --> 00:20:24,625
RIGHT NOW, I'M THE LUCKIEST
GUY ON THE PLANET.

352
00:20:38,666 --> 00:20:39,958
- ( engine revs )

353
00:20:44,416 --> 00:20:47,375
- AT THE END OF THAT LAST ROUND,
I WAS PUSHING IT FULL TILT.

354
00:20:50,125 --> 00:20:52,333
THIS MAKES ME REMEMBER
WHY I STARTED RACING

355
00:20:52,416 --> 00:20:53,750
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

356
00:20:53,833 --> 00:20:55,375
YOU'VE BEEN ONE HELL
OF AN OPPONENT,

357
00:20:55,458 --> 00:20:58,458
BUT IN THIS ROUND, KID,
I'M WIPING YOU OFF THE MAP.

358
00:21:11,166 --> 00:21:12,458
- ( theme song playing )

359
00:21:25,583 --> 00:21:27,000
- ( singing in Japanese )

360
00:23:10,375 --> 00:23:11,541
- Announcer: EACH WITH
THEIR OWN HOPES,

361
00:23:11,625 --> 00:23:13,708
EACH WITH THEIR OWN DESIRES.

362
00:23:13,791 --> 00:23:15,916
NEXT ON INITIAL D
SECOND STAGE,

363
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:19,916
IT'S OUR LAST EPISODE OF THE
SEASON, "CHANGING SEASONS."

364
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:21,250
DON'T MISS IT.

